text:
Hudson Street, east side, north from Thomas Street. The block of buildings (in the foreground) from Thomas to Worth Streets were razed, and on their site now (1937) stands the 24-story Western Union Building.

October 25, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.

Thomas Street (left), at the S.B. corner of Hudson Street (right, where Thomas Street terminates), showing work in progress at the N.E. corner, for the Western Union Building. Buildings at the right are on Hudson Street. August 2, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
